.TH lshp 1 "October 1994" "Scilab Group" "Scilab macro"
.so man1/sci.an
.SH NAME 
lshp - length shortest path  
.SH CALLING SEQUENCE
.nf
[p,lp] = lshp(i,j,[g])
.fi
.SH PARAMETERS
.TP 4
i,j 
: integers, node numbers
.TP 2
g
: graph list, optional argument with default value \fVthe_g\fR
.TP 2
p
: row vector of arc numbers
.TP 3
lp
: shortest length
.SH DESCRIPTION
\fVlshp\fR returns the shortest path \fVp\fR in length from
node\fVi\fR to node \fVj\fR. \fVlp\fR is the length of this path.
.SH SEE ALSO
anshp, lshp, ns2p
